claim: Benedict Arnold commanded fortifications at West Point, New York and was going to surrender to the British.
premise_source_doc_sentence: While a general on the American side , he obtained command of the fortifications at West Point , New York  (  future site of the U.S. Military Academy after 1802  )  overlooking the cliffs at the Hudson River  (  upriver from British-occupied New York City  )  , and planned to surrender it to the British forces .
